<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1627,2020]" pageId="11" pageNumber="372">Yellowish, head with spot pattern often largely confluent in male, ocelli red, often dark markings enlarged on body with faint smoky tint on forewing.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1627,2020]" pageId="11" pageNumber="372">
Male abdomen. 
<number box="[386,400,1738,1762]" pageId="11" pageNumber="372" value="2.0">2</number>
nd acrotergite with trunk widely V-shaped, neck thin, apparently shorter than half of trunk width. 
<number box="[229,243,1777,1801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="372" value="2.0">2</number>
nd tergal apodeme reaching middle of tergite posteriorly. 
<number box="[877,891,1777,1801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="372" value="1.0">1</number>
st sternal apodeme with posterior lobes about 
<number box="[1401,1436,1776,1801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="372" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as wide. 
<number box="[404,418,1816,1840]" pageId="11" pageNumber="372" value="2.0">2</number>
nd sternal apodeme with posterior lobes reduced, shorter than basal width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1627,2020]" pageId="11" pageNumber="372">Male genitalia. Aedeagus robust, with serrate lateral margin; aedeagal shaft extending to near middle laterally; apex of apical appendages convergent, touching or crossed slightly.</paragraph>
